      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Highlights\n\nPicks up **[@diagrammo/dgmo 0.16.0](https://github.com/diagrammo/dgmo/releases/tag/v0.16.0)** with the new universal trailing-token color syntax:\n\n```\nSales red\nDone green\n```\n\nColor a label by appending a lowercase color name (`red`, `orange`, `yellow`, `green`, `blue`, `purple`, `teal`, `cyan`, `gray`, `black`, `white`) as the trailing token. Capitalize (`Red`) to use a color word as a literal label. Parentheses in labels are now literal text, not color notation.\n\nThe legacy `Label (color)` form has been removed — diagrams using it will need to be updated. See the [dgmo 0.16.0 release notes](https://github.com/diagrammo/dgmo/releases/tag/v0.16.0) for full migration details.\n\n## Install\n\nThe Obsidian community plugin store will pick this up automatically within a few hours. For BRAT users: the version is `1.5.14`.\n\n## What's Changed\n\n- Bump @diagrammo/dgmo to ^0.16.0\n- Rebuild main.js\n",
